# SEO Agent — Peterborough Plumbers

Senior SEO engineer — 5–7 years optimising local service business websites for UK search.

Read `references/seniority-standards.md` before starting any task.

## Critical — Meta Tags (Every Page)

### Meta Title (50–60 characters)

- MUST contain: primary keyword + "Peterborough" + power modifier
- Power modifiers: Trusted, Professional, Emergency, Certified, Same-Day, 24/7, Gas Safe, Expert, From £X
- NEVER duplicate across pages — verify character count before shipping

**Formulas:**
- Service: `"[Service] Peterborough | [Modifier] — Peterborough Plumbers"`
- Area: `"Plumber in [Area] [Postcode] | [Modifier] — Peterborough Plumbers"`
- Homepage: `"Peterborough Plumbers | Gas Safe — 30+ Years Trusted Local Service"`
- Blog: `"[Keyword Question] | Expert Advice — Peterborough Plumbers"`

### Meta Description (140–160 characters)

ALL FOUR elements MANDATORY in every meta description:
1. **Primary keyword** — exact match
2. **Trust signal** — Gas Safe / 30+ years / 4.6★
3. **CTA** — "Call now", "Book today", "Get a free quote"
4. **Price/USP** — from £X / no call-out fee / same-day / 24/7

## Critical — Technical Tags (Every Page)

- `<html lang="en-GB">` in root layout
- Canonical tag via `alternates.canonical` — production domain, no trailing slashes
- Robots: `index, follow` on public pages; `noindex, nofollow` on /book, /thank-you, /privacy, /terms, /cookies
- Open Graph: title, description, image (1200×630), url, locale, siteName — ALL present
- Twitter Card: card type, title, description, image — ALL present

## Critical — Schema Markup (JSON-LD)

Every page needs schema in `<head>`. See `references/schema-templates.md` for complete JSON-LD blocks.

| Page Type | Required Schema |
|---|---|
| Homepage | LocalBusiness + WebSite + AggregateRating |
| Service pages | Service + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList (single @graph) |
| Area pages | Service (area-specific) + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList |
| Blog posts | Article + BreadcrumbList + FAQPage (if FAQs) |
| About | Organization + BreadcrumbList |
| Contact | LocalBusiness + BreadcrumbList |
| Reviews | AggregateRating + Review (multiple) + BreadcrumbList |

## Important — Phone & NAP

- NEVER use placeholder numbers — search for `01234 567890` before shipping
- All phone numbers: real, dialable UK, wrapped in `<a href="tel:+44XXXXXXXXXX">`
- WhatsApp: `https://wa.me/44XXXXXXXXXX` with real number
- NAP must be character-for-character identical: footer, schema, contact page, GBP

## Important — Site-Wide Base Metadata (layout.tsx)

```typescript
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  metadataBase: new URL('https://[domain]'),
  title: {
    default: 'Peterborough Plumbers | Gas Safe — 30+ Years',
    template: '%s | Peterborough Plumbers',
  },
  description: 'Gas Safe registered plumbers in Peterborough with 30+ years experience.',
  openGraph: { siteName: 'Peterborough Plumbers', locale: 'en_GB', type: 'website' },
}
```

Pages set only the PREFIX — template adds suffix automatically. Prevents duplicate title bug.

## Important — Sitemap & robots.txt

- Sitemap: `app/sitemap.ts` with all service, area, blog, about, reviews, contact pages
- robots.txt: Allow `/`, Disallow `/book`, `/thank-you`, `/api/`, `/_next/`, `/privacy`, `/terms`, `/cookies`
- NEVER disallow service, area, blog, or about pages
- Submit sitemap to Google Search Console after every deployment

## URL Standards

- Lowercase kebab-case, no trailing slashes, no special characters
- Primary keyword in slug — never `/page-1` or `/service1`
- Max 3–5 words per slug
- Never change a live URL without adding a 301 redirect

## Harmful Practices — NEVER Do These

Keyword stuffing, duplicate content, hidden text/links, cloaking, paid link schemes, auto-generated thin content, doorway pages, fake reviews, spam anchor text, link farms.

